x4freetext: Each neutron detector bank is constructed
from either BF3 or He-3 detectors. The BF3 counter
banks cover an area of 8 x 20 in. The He-3 bank
consists of up to 5 one-inch thick detectors 20 in.
in length filled to a pressure of 10 atm.
6 m flight path, additional 2m from target to
detectors. Typically, the detectors are located at
150 deg. Measurement of the scattering kernel
dsigma/dthetadE, in units of barn per steradian per
electron-volt per molecule of scattering material,
uses a comparison technique, with vanadium as the
standard. The scattering cross section from vanadium
is well known to be incoherent and elastic with the
scattered neutron energy very nearly equal to the
ingoing incident energy. When this comparison
